This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of Digital Libraries (cs.DL) as it deals with bibliometric assessment of individuals and their publication activity. It could also belong to Information Retrieval (cs.IR) as it discusses the use of indicators to measure performance on an individual author-level. Additionally, it could be classified under Cybersecurity (cs.CY) as it examines the complexity of calculations and data-collection demands. It may also fall under Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) as it discusses the impact of output and citations. Finally, it could be categorized under Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) as it deals with ranking and impact over time.
